    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Silver gelatin, or silver halide, black and white prints on a fiber base, or RC-base paper, and having a digital component. Silver gelatin paper is exposed in a photographic laser printer from a digital file, then processed in liquid photo chemistry. These may have archival qualities and a completely neutral image tone.</Note_Text>
